        "timestamp": "2019-02-26 18:23:51.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIs this a draft? or final? i had noticed some comments.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "b38d7da97706f4d37269de108cff5ec6d468f240",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 137,
          "name": "Alexis de Talhouet",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "adetalhouet89@gmail.com",
          "username": "adetalhouet"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-02-26 18:35:17.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Is this a draft? or final? i had noticed some comments.\n\nThis is pretty much done for now. Team is bbuilding BBs for config-assign and config-deploy, they will remove the TODO and put the logic in there when ready. Remaining is add the properties in OOM, but I'm taking care of that.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "1afd24d314c1c8767d43ecbd4f896b579838d55f",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 63,
          "name": "Steve Smokowski",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ss835w@att.com",
          "username": "SteveSmokowski"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-02-26 19:00:54.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nDid you really need to introduce grpc here as a client?  We already have multiple base clients around.  It just seems like another layer to support.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "87f7fdf1acb4eb42c52c56b32d809ec73eb56ea4",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 137,
          "name": "Alexis de Talhouet",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "adetalhouet89@gmail.com",
          "username": "adetalhouet"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-02-26 19:09:04.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Did you really need to introduce grpc here as a client? \n\nYes, reason for this is gRPC is HTTP2 based, hence I can have a streaming based communication between SO and CDS. Also, no need to manipulate URI, everything is based on .proto messages defined in CDS: https://github.com/onap/ccsdk-apps/tree/master/components/model-catalog/proto-definition/proto\n\nPoint of gRPC is, SO will send one request to CDS through that stream, and CDS will respond back with many sub-responses to update SO of the current status of the request. We're doing this because we were told SO is the place to have status of request being updated.\n\nWe had a few design session call with Seshu, Gil, Yuriy, and I thought even you were a part of it. We could hold on merging that code and have a follow-up call to",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "eab17381f48491a54f3eda1d0557e2692be90f42",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 63,
          "name": "Steve Smokowski",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ss835w@att.com",
          "username": "SteveSmokowski"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-02-26 19:14:26.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nAdd some unit tests, and we should be good here.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "01805cb1c386159e93bfba2f4bdcaa0a87dad1e4",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 137,
          "name": "Alexis de Talhouet",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "adetalhouet89@gmail.com",
          "username": "adetalhouet"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-02-26 19:15:18.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\n> Add some unit tests, and we should be good here.\n\nSure, I'll do that. thank you",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
